aviour_Analysis_TDWR.ppt','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:252'),(22094,'identifier',12,'http://www.edshare.soton.ac.uk/252/3/Introduction_to_Behaviour_Analysis_TDWR.pdf','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:252'),(22095,'identifier',12,'An Introduction to Behaviour Analysis - Tom Randell\n Keywords:behaviour analysis, behaviour, behavior analysis, behavior, experimental analysis of behavior, experimental analysis of behaviour, applied behaviour analysis, applied behavior analysis, ABA, Skinner, radical behaviourism, radical behaviorism, showcase \n','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:252'),(22096,'relation',12,'http://www.edshare.soton.ac.uk/252/','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:252'),(22097,'title',12,'A Self-Scoring Exercise On APA Style, Research Language, and Referencing for Undergraduate Students','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22098,'creator',12,'Freimuth, Marilyn','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22099,'description',12,'Based on examples provided by 27 graduate psychology faculty, this self-test incorporates many of the more common errors in style, language, and referencing found in student papers. Taking this self-test helps students to recognize common errors and encourages them to refer the APA Publication Manual on a regular basis. In addition, students begin to think about how to use correctly the language of psychological research.\r\nThis self-test should take about 30 minutes to complete and score. It is composed of three parts:\r\n\r\na) a mock Discussion section, where students are asked to act as editors and find the errors, p. 2 (10\r\nminutes).\r\n\r\nb) a corrected Discussion section, where students find the errors they missed, p. 3 (5 minutes)\r\nand,\r\n\r\nc) a full description of each error with illustrations of correct usage, pp. 4-7 (15 minutes).\r\n\r\nThis exercise assumes some knowledge of APA style. Thus, it is best-suited for advanced undergraduates who need to write research reports and all levels of graduate students. It may be taken at home or in class. Although the self-test is designed to be fully self-directed, instructors may wish to use it at the beginning or end of a classroom discussion on APA style. It could also be used in a pre-test-post-test fashion to evaluate students learning over the course of a term.','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22100,'date',12,'2008-06-03','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22101,'type',12,'Resource','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22102,'type',12,'NonPeerReviewed','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22103,'format',12,'application/vnd.edshare-link','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22104,'identifier',12,'http://www.uni-hamburg.de/fachbereiche-einrichtungen/fb16/absozpsy/Uebungen_zum_APA_Style.pdf','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22105,'identifier',12,'A Self-Scoring Exercise On APA Style, Research Language, and Referencing for Undergraduate Students - Marilyn Freimuth\n Keywords:APA style, Psychology, Research language, American Psychological Association, Referencing \n','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22106,'relation',12,'http://www.edshare.soton.ac.uk/272/','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:272'),(22107,'title',12,'Illiers Combray','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:276'),(22108,'creator',12,'Douglas, Helen','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:276'),(22109,'creator',12,'Irvine, Zoe','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:276'),(22110,'description',12,'Artists\' Book.  This is a concertina artist book, included in the collection held at Winchester School of Art Library.  The Word document presents a commentary on the book and its links to the place, Illiers Combray in France and Marcel Proust.','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:276'),(22111,'date',12,'2008-06-10','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:276'),(22112,'type',12,'Resource','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:276'),(22113,'type',12,'NonPeerReviewed','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:276'),(22114,'format',12,'application/msword','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:276'),(22115,'format',12,'image/jpeg','oai:edshare.soton.ac.uk:276'),(22116,'identifier',12,'http://www.edshare.soton.ac.uk/276/2/Helen_Douglas_text.doc','oai:edshare.soton.